<subSubSection pageNumber="876" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="876">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">Note:</emphasis>
This name has often been treated as ambiguous (see discussion by Moraldo in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">Webbia</emphasis>
40: 227-228. 1986) and informally rejected in favour of e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Breistr." authorityName="Breistr." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="offneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">S. offneri</emphasis>
Breistr.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1762" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capillata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">S. capillata</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="celakovskyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">S. celakovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martinovský">Martinovsky</normalizedToken>
. See extensive discussion by the typifying authors who conclude that they prefer to typify the name in the sense of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Stipa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="celakovskyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="876">S. celakovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and to allow the Linnaean name to be applied in this sense.
</paragraph>
